# React Query Patterns

## Role-Based Data Fetching

Use React Query with role-aware query keys and conditional endpoints.

### Query Key Patterns
Include role information in query keys to prevent cache conflicts:

```typescript
// Role-specific cache keys
const { data } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ["activities", role], // Include role in key
  queryFn: () => fetchActivities(role),
  enabled: !loading
});

// Entity-specific with role context
const { data } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ["pentest", pentestId, role],
  queryFn: () => fetchPentest(pentestId, role),
  enabled: !!pentestId && !loading
});
```

### Conditional Endpoint Selection
Always use role-based endpoint selection:

```typescript
const { data: vulnerability } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ["pentest", pentestId, "vulnerability", vulnerabilityId],
  queryFn: () => {
    if (isClient()) {
      return axiosInstance.get(apiRoutes.client.pentests.vulnerabilities.details(pentestId!, vulnerabilityId!));
    } else if (isPentester()) {
      return axiosInstance.get(apiRoutes.pentester.vulnerabilities.details(pentestId!, vulnerabilityId!));
    } else {
      return axiosInstance.get(apiRoutes.pentests.vulnerabilities.details(pentestId!, vulnerabilityId!));
    }
  },
  enabled: !loading && !!pentestId && !!vulnerabilityId
});
```

### Mutation Patterns
Use role-based mutations with appropriate error handling:

```typescript
const { mutate: updateStatus, isPending } = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (status: string) => {
    if (isClient()) {
      return axiosInstance.patch(apiRoutes.client.pentests.vulnerabilities.status(pentestId!, vulnerabilityId!), { status });
    } else if (isPentester()) {
      return axiosInstance.patch(apiRoutes.pentester.vulnerabilities.updateStatus(pentestId!, vulnerabilityId!), { status });
    } else {
      return axiosInstance.patch(apiRoutes.pentests.vulnerabilities.status(pentestId!, vulnerabilityId!), { status });
    }
  },
  onSuccess: () => {
    refetchVulnerability();
    toast({ title: "Status updated", description: "Vulnerability status has been updated successfully" });
  }
});
```

### Loading State Management
Always check for user loading state before enabling queries:

```typescript
const { data } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ["data", id],
  queryFn: () => fetchData(id),
  enabled: !loading && !!id // Wait for user to load
});
```

### Query Dependencies
- Import [useUser hook](mdc:src/hooks/useUser.ts) for role checking
- Import [toast hook](mdc:src/hooks/use-toast.ts) for notifications
- Use [AxiosInstance](mdc:src/lib/AxiosInstance.ts) for all API calls
